<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-09-01T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-09-01T06:00:00-05:00" n="456" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d456">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">701.6552/7: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Third Secretary of Embassy in Spain</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wendelin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-09-01T11:00:00+00:00">September 1, 1936—11
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received September 1—10:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>X–116. Italian Embassy will leave Madrid for Alicante tonight, so
                                informed Spanish Government last night and requests us not to make
                                this public until their departure. Departure of German<note n="63" xml:id="d456fn63">The German Chargé and staff left Madrid by
                                    plane for Alicante on August 30 (701.6252/16).</note> and
                                Italian Embassies and arrival of Russian Ambassador are clearly for
                                political reasons and may herald important international
                                developments. Russian Ambassador presented letters of credence to
                                President of Spanish Republic August 29.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wendelin</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>